♪ <i>This town is named for you</i> ♪

487
00:22:58,333 --> 00:23:01,333
"For You" is a weird name for a town.

488
00:23:01,416 --> 00:23:03,583
Uh, I'm sorry, but who are you?

489
00:23:03,666 --> 00:23:04,916
Oh, ha!

490
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:09,125
Forgive me! I'm Angus,
the groundskeeper here at Loud Castle.

491
00:23:09,208 --> 00:23:12,916
And I welcome you to your ancestral home!

492
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,208
[Louds gasps]

493
00:23:14,291 --> 00:23:16,666
- Sweet!
- So fancy.

494
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:19,500
- This is more like it.
- Wowie, wow.

495
00:23:19,583 --> 00:23:22,291
I can't believe Louds lived here.

496
00:23:22,375 --> 00:23:25,083
We could fit 100 of our houses in here.

497
00:23:25,166 --> 00:23:27,666
[whimsical music playing]

498
00:23:31,666 --> 00:23:33,083
Oh me, oh my!

499
00:23:33,708 --> 00:23:37,916
Do my eyes deceive me? Why, you're, um...

500
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:39,125
Louds!

501
00:23:39,208 --> 00:23:44,208
Yes, I heard the song, Angus.
Everyone in Scotland heard the song.

502
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:49,166
Our dreams have come true, Morag!
Louds are back after 400 years.

503
00:23:49,250 --> 00:23:50,791
Oh, my!

504
00:23:50,875 --> 00:23:53,750
Put me down!

505
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:55,875
Oh! Sorry. Sorry.

506
00:23:55,958 --> 00:24:00,541
Loud family, may I introduce Morag,
the castle caretaker.

507
00:24:00,625 --> 00:24:03,833
Oh! Would you care to take my bag?

508
00:24:03,916 --> 00:24:06,125
Lola! Sorry.

509
00:24:06,208 --> 00:24:10,000
I can barely believe Louds have returned
to their rightful place.

510
00:24:10,083 --> 00:24:11,625
Well, for a week.

511
00:24:12,125 --> 00:24:14,541
A week? Not forevermore?

512
00:24:14,625 --> 00:24:16,375
Oh, let's not pry, Angus.

513
00:24:16,458 --> 00:24:19,125
The family is only here on holiday.

514
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:21,416
Yes, well, I do hope you enjoy your visit.

515
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:23,958
You'll find lovely accommodations
in the village.

516
00:24:24,041 --> 00:24:27,166
Or they could stay here!
It's their family's castle after all.

517
00:24:27,250 --> 00:24:28,500
- You mean it?
- We can stay?

518
00:24:28,583 --> 00:24:29,750
[all cheering] Yes!

519
00:24:30,583 --> 00:24:33,250
What a marvelous idea.

520
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:34,500
[cheering]

521
00:24:34,583 --> 00:24:37,875
- I've never been so excited.
- Can we call you Aunty Morag?

522
00:24:37,958 --> 00:24:40,958
- [gasps] Oi! Hands off the antiques.
- Oh!

523
00:24:42,791 --> 00:24:45,083
- Oh, my.
- It was like that already.

524
00:24:45,666 --> 00:24:47,625
- [crashing]
- [cat meows]

525
00:24:48,125 --> 00:24:49,458
[chuckles] That one's on me.

526
00:24:49,541 --> 00:24:53,166
Uh, Mr. Angus, sir,
what can you tell us about our ancestors?

527
00:24:53,250 --> 00:24:56,625
Oh! A grander clan
this land has never seen!

528
00:24:58,416 --> 00:25:00,166
- [Luna] Whoa!
- [Lola] No way!

529
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:02,625
Am I experiencing double vision?

530
00:25:02,708 --> 00:25:04,583
It's old-timey us!

531
00:25:04,666 --> 00:25:06,625
When did we pose for this?

532
00:25:06,708 --> 00:25:10,375
[Lori] Ten girls and one boy.
Literally just like us.

533
00:25:10,458 --> 00:25:11,500
That's amazing.

534
00:25:11,583 --> 00:25:12,500
Yes!

535
00:25:12,583 --> 00:25:14,375
Yeah. How about that?

536
00:25:15,708 --> 00:25:18,625
Just a week. Only for a week.

537
00:25:18,708 --> 00:25:21,041
Would you fancy a look
at the rest of the castle?

538
00:25:21,125 --> 00:25:21,958
[all] Yes!

539
00:25:22,041 --> 00:25:24,791
[Luan] Last one to their room
is a Scotch egg. Get it?

540
00:25:24,875 --> 00:25:26,666
- [Leni] No, I don't.
- No touching!

541
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:27,916
[screams]

542
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,333
It's just impossible to find
good help these days.

543
00:25:31,416 --> 00:25:32,500
- [Luan] Woo-hoo!
- Oh!

544
00:25:32,583 --> 00:25:36,791
No roughhousing. Hey, you!
Hey, hands off the tapestries. Tapestries!

545
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:41,958
So, let me guess.
The sisters were all special, right?

546
00:25:42,041 --> 00:25:44,708
Oh, aye! All were exceptional.

547
00:25:44,791 --> 00:25:48,875
Our loch has never seen anything
quite like the Loud lassies!

548
00:25:49,458 --> 00:25:50,458
Of course.

549
00:25:51,291 --> 00:25:52,583
But there was also...

550
00:25:52,666 --> 00:25:53,750
- Stinkin!
- Lincoln!

551
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:55,541
- Come here.
- Hurry!

552
00:25:55,625 --> 00:25:57,625
- Chop, chop!
- Sorry, Angus, I gotta go.

553
00:25:57,708 --> 00:25:58,833
What? What is it?

554
00:25:58,916 --> 00:26:00,416
[Lori] You have to see this.

555
00:26:02,125 --> 00:26:03,541
Wow! Look at this!

556
00:26:04,500 --> 00:26:06,250
We all get our own rooms!

557
00:26:06,333 --> 00:26:08,000
[sisters] Lincoln, come look.

558
00:26:08,083 --> 00:26:10,083
I can jam in peace.

559
00:26:10,958 --> 00:26:11,958
Cool.

560
00:26:12,375 --> 00:26:14,083
I can rest in peace.

561
00:26:14,166 --> 00:26:15,166
Spooky.

562
00:26:15,583 --> 00:26:16,583
Whoa!

563
00:26:16,625 --> 00:26:19,791
No more tea parties
ruined by Lana's burping.

564
00:26:19,875 --> 00:26:21,291
Wanna bet?

565
00:26:21,375 --> 00:26:23,375
- [belches loudly]
- [laughs]

566
00:26:23,458 --> 00:26:25,083
My room has a hot tub.

567
00:26:25,958 --> 00:26:27,291
Yeah, I noticed.

568
00:26:27,375 --> 00:26:28,625
Whoa!

569
00:26:29,416 --> 00:26:31,750
I've found my happy place.

570
00:26:31,833 --> 00:26:33,416
- [explosion]
- Boom-boom!

571
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:35,416
Mine has a fashion runway!

572
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:36,625
[Lincoln] Styling!

573
00:26:37,208 --> 00:26:40,000
- [mic feedback]
- Mine is big enough to be a comedy club.

574
00:26:40,083 --> 00:26:42,416
[laughs] We each have our own bathroom!

575
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:43,500
[all] What?

576
00:26:43,541 --> 00:26:46,000
I'm gonna take like 100 leaks a day.

577
00:26:46,083 --> 00:26:47,625
- [toilet flushes]
- [screams]

578
00:26:48,166 --> 00:26:50,333
- Ah, there you are, lad.
- [Lily giggles]

579
00:26:51,083 --> 00:26:53,958
Before you were whisked away,
I tried to tell you

580
00:26:54,041 --> 00:26:58,083
that the most special
of all your ancestors was the duke.

581
00:26:58,166 --> 00:26:59,375
The duke?

582
00:26:59,458 --> 00:27:03,541
Aye. And don't you know,
you'll be staying in his room.

583
00:27:05,166 --> 00:27:06,166
[gasps]

584
00:27:08,375 --> 00:27:09,458
Whoa!

585
00:27:10,875 --> 00:27:15,041
Wait. The boy in the painting
was the duke?

586
00:27:15,125 --> 00:27:17,041
- Aye.
- Hang on.

587
00:27:17,125 --> 00:27:20,125
The boy in the painting
with the white hair was the duke?

588
00:27:20,208 --> 00:27:21,083
Aye.

589
00:27:21,166 --> 00:27:24,541
The boy in the painting
with the white hair that had ten sisters

590
00:27:24,625 --> 00:27:26,916
and looked just like me was the duke?

591
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:28,000
The one and only!

592
00:27:28,083 --> 00:27:30,583
He was the most special Loud
there ever was.

593
00:27:30,666 --> 00:27:31,708
Yes!

594
00:27:32,583 --> 00:27:35,250
[Angus] Far and wide people knew his name.

595
00:27:35,333 --> 00:27:38,916
His deeds were noble. His heart was stout!

596
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,125
- Whoa!
- Whoa!

597
00:27:40,208 --> 00:27:41,833
Sweet digs, Stinkin.

598
00:27:41,916 --> 00:27:44,083
The boy was the duke!

599
00:27:44,166 --> 00:27:46,333
Whatever tugs your tonsils, bro.

600
00:27:46,416 --> 00:27:49,041
Hey, Angus, what's the deal
with all the dragon stuff?

601
00:27:49,125 --> 00:27:51,125
Ah, so you noticed!

602
00:27:51,208 --> 00:27:53,916
If it's dragons you fancy,
there's something you should see.

603
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,625
- [Lana] Ha!
- [Angus] Come with me.

604
00:27:55,708 --> 00:27:56,708
[gasps]

605
00:27:57,666 --> 00:27:58,875
Whoa.

606
00:27:58,958 --> 00:28:02,000
[noble music playing]

607
00:28:03,791 --> 00:28:08,583
The reason why dragons are celebrated here
is that they are a part of our history.

608
00:28:08,666 --> 00:28:11,041
I knew it! Dragons are for reals.

609
00:28:11,125 --> 00:28:13,166
[imitates buzzer] Sounds like hooey to me!

610
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:15,541
Oh, they're as real
as the tartan in my kilt.

611
00:28:16,083 --> 00:28:19,750
In fact, your ancestors
had their very own dragon.

612
00:28:19,833 --> 00:28:22,333
And when the family left, so did she.

613
00:28:26,708 --> 00:28:28,791
Whoa, a dragon cave!

614
00:28:28,875 --> 00:28:30,000
Keep dreaming.

615
00:28:30,083 --> 00:28:31,791
If it's proof you need,

616
00:28:31,875 --> 00:28:35,666
take a gander at what
your ancestors' dragon left behind.

617
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:38,708
Whoa! Oh, man. I told you!

618
00:28:38,791 --> 00:28:40,291
This is wack-a-doodle!

619
00:28:40,375 --> 00:28:43,458
Miss Lynn, if you wouldn't mind
taking Miss Lily for a moment.

620
00:28:43,541 --> 00:28:44,375
[giggles]

621
00:28:44,458 --> 00:28:47,166
Just as we hoped
that someday Louds would return,

622
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:50,125
we hoped a dragon would too.

623
00:28:50,625 --> 00:28:52,833
[gasps] It's hatched!

624
00:28:52,916 --> 00:28:55,083
You mean there's a dragon
on the loose in here?

625
00:28:55,166 --> 00:28:57,458
- Uh-oh.
- No sudden movements.

626
00:28:57,541 --> 00:29:00,250
Easy does it. Remain calm!

627
00:29:00,333 --> 00:29:01,250
[both] Angus!

628
00:29:01,333 --> 00:29:03,125
Ah! Run for your lives!

629
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:04,500
[shouting]

630
00:29:04,583 --> 00:29:06,375
[laughing]

631
00:29:07,333 --> 00:29:09,208
- Aw, so cute.
- Puppy dragon.

632
00:29:09,291 --> 00:29:11,208
Look at that little face.

633
00:29:11,291 --> 00:29:14,000
- [chuckles]
- We gotta name this little pup.

634
00:29:15,416 --> 00:29:16,666
Lela.

635
00:29:17,416 --> 00:29:19,166
[Lana] Her name is Lela.

636
00:29:19,250 --> 00:29:20,625
[Luan] I love her so much.

637
00:29:20,708 --> 00:29:21,833
She's so cute.

638
00:29:21,916 --> 00:29:24,666
Biologically improbable yet so adorable.

639
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:26,291
Can we keep her?

640
00:29:26,375 --> 00:29:29,375
Okay. But I am not changing her diaper.

641
00:29:29,458 --> 00:29:30,875
- Yes!
- Thanks, Mom.

642
00:29:30,958 --> 00:29:33,166
[trumpet playing off-key]

643
00:29:33,250 --> 00:29:35,125
Dude, pick a key.

644
00:29:35,208 --> 00:29:36,458
[trumpet sputters]

645
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:37,625
[trumpet clatters]

646
00:29:37,708 --> 00:29:40,583
[noble music playing]

647
00:29:42,291 --> 00:29:44,375
Uh, what are you doing, honey?

648
00:29:44,458 --> 00:29:46,166
Duke-ing.

649
00:29:46,291 --> 00:29:47,583
Right in front of us?

650
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:50,000
You know we have our own bathrooms now.

651
00:29:50,083 --> 00:29:51,875
[laughing]

652
00:29:51,958 --> 00:29:53,958
[regal music playing]

653
00:29:59,541 --> 00:30:00,541
Hmm?

654
00:30:02,875 --> 00:30:03,875
Hmm.

655
00:30:07,083 --> 00:30:08,208
[trumpet sputters]

656
00:30:08,291 --> 00:30:09,791
[all laughing]

657
00:30:09,875 --> 00:30:11,708
Nice toilet paper scarf.

658
00:30:11,791 --> 00:30:14,083
Seriously? Pantaloons this time of year?

659
00:30:14,166 --> 00:30:17,833
I think Lincoln's gone
a little panta-looney. Get it?

660
00:30:18,791 --> 00:30:20,291
[exclaims] What the what?

661
00:30:20,958 --> 00:30:23,291
At least someone knows royalty
when they see it.

662
00:30:23,375 --> 00:30:27,666
The rest of you might wanna get on board.
'Cause this Loud is about to rule.

663
00:30:28,250 --> 00:30:30,708
- Dinner is served.
- [Lincoln] I'm okay.

664
00:30:30,791 --> 00:30:33,208
- I cooked everything in the castle.
- Whoa!

665
00:30:33,291 --> 00:30:35,750
I ran out of garlic, so I used Gaelic.

666
00:30:35,833 --> 00:30:37,375
[laughs] Good one, Dad.

667
00:30:41,958 --> 00:30:44,166
- [all cheering]
- [Luan] I call the turkey!

668
00:30:44,250 --> 00:30:45,500
Save some for me.

669
00:30:45,583 --> 00:30:47,041
[Lana] Yay, burritos!

670
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,666
This is all your doing.

671
00:30:49,750 --> 00:30:51,333
It was my pleasure.

672
00:30:51,416 --> 00:30:52,708
[screams]

673
00:30:55,666 --> 00:30:56,666
What a day!

674
00:30:56,750 --> 00:30:59,083
The Louds are back and so is a dragon.

675
00:30:59,166 --> 00:31:00,833
[laughs gleefully]

676
00:31:01,416 --> 00:31:02,416
[Lily giggles]

677
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:06,666
Bawitotos.

678
00:31:06,750 --> 00:31:07,833
[sniffs]

679
00:31:07,916 --> 00:31:09,500
[whimpers]

680
00:31:10,833 --> 00:31:11,958
[coos]

681
00:31:15,083 --> 00:31:16,291
[giggles]

682
00:31:16,375 --> 00:31:18,500
I'm so glad we did this.

683
00:31:18,583 --> 00:31:21,958
[in Scottish accent] Aye, m'lady.
What a happy clan we have.

684
00:31:22,500 --> 00:31:24,000
Thanks, Angus.

685
00:31:24,083 --> 00:31:25,750
- Mmm.
- [Lily] Bawitos.

686
00:31:25,833 --> 00:31:29,000
So, what's a guy got to do
to become the duke around here?

687
00:31:29,083 --> 00:31:29,916
Come again?

688
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,333
I was thinking about it,
and the duke and I look alike,

689
00:31:33,416 --> 00:31:37,791
we both have ten sisters, white hair,
a turkey tail, we're the same height...

690
00:31:38,625 --> 00:31:39,833
Dragon.

691
00:31:40,791 --> 00:31:41,875
[giggles]

692
00:31:42,291 --> 00:31:43,833
- [stomach grumbles]
- [moans]

693
00:31:43,916 --> 00:31:45,500
Whoa!

694
00:31:45,583 --> 00:31:47,708
Holy moly, she grows fast.

695
00:31:47,791 --> 00:31:49,166
Big girl!

696
00:31:49,250 --> 00:31:50,291
[all laugh]

697
00:31:50,375 --> 00:31:54,666
So the way I see it,
A plus B equals me being the new duke!

698
00:31:54,750 --> 00:31:55,958
What do you think?

699
00:31:56,041 --> 00:31:59,041
Lincoln, I'm afraid
it's not that simple, lad.

700
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:03,083
[sighs] Wisely spoken.
You should listen to Angus.

701
00:32:03,166 --> 00:32:06,166
One can only become the duke
by making life better

702
00:32:06,250 --> 00:32:08,125
for the people and our village.

703
00:32:08,208 --> 00:32:09,750
I see.

704
00:32:09,833 --> 00:32:12,375
Help the town and become the duke.

705
00:32:13,208 --> 00:32:14,416
Piece of cake.

706
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:17,000
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I've got work to do.

707
00:32:17,083 --> 00:32:20,416
'Cause tomorrow, I'm gonna duke
this town up! Oh, yeah!

708
00:32:21,166 --> 00:32:25,083
You fool! Blathering on
to that featherbrained boy

709
00:32:25,166 --> 00:32:26,791
about becoming the duke!

710
00:32:26,875 --> 00:32:29,250
Oh, the people would love a new duke.

711
00:32:29,333 --> 00:32:32,208
[imitating Angus]
"Oh, the people would love a new duke.”

712
00:32:32,291 --> 00:32:34,958
[normal voice] I don't care a jot
about those peasants!

713
00:32:35,041 --> 00:32:38,666
They're not peasants, Morag.
They're our neighbors, friends.

714
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,500
Enough with your twaddle!

715
00:32:40,583 --> 00:32:44,500
Thanks to you flapping your gob,
I'm stuck with these hooligans!

716
00:32:44,583 --> 00:32:47,875
Crashing through the crowded halls,
dodging girls like...

717
00:32:47,958 --> 00:32:51,083
- Ping pong balls?
- Just to reach the bathroom on time.

718
00:32:51,166 --> 00:32:52,750
[chuckles] That's rather catchy.

719
00:32:52,833 --> 00:32:54,875
Don't you get cheeky with me.

720
00:32:54,958 --> 00:32:58,958
My ancestors have cared
for this castle in peace and quiet

721
00:32:59,041 --> 00:33:01,250
ever since they drove away the...

722
00:33:01,333 --> 00:33:06,791
I mean, ever since the, you know,
the first Louds sailed away forever.

723
00:33:06,875 --> 00:33:11,958
Oh, I deserve better than
to be banished to your wretched hovel.

724
00:33:12,041 --> 00:33:13,666
It's only for a week.

725
00:33:14,666 --> 00:33:18,500
And you'll have oodles of quietness here
in my little castle.

726
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:21,791
Shall I give you the grand t... Oof.

727
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:22,750
Oh.

728
00:33:22,833 --> 00:33:24,208
Good night, Morag.

729
00:33:25,916 --> 00:33:27,916
[owl hooting]

730
00:33:28,791 --> 00:33:32,166
[dreamy music playing]

731
00:33:37,041 --> 00:33:39,833
Castle spirits, hear my plea.

732
00:33:39,916 --> 00:33:42,958
I summon a Loud from my family.

733
00:33:43,041 --> 00:33:46,083
On mystic winds, across Scottish moors,

734
00:33:46,166 --> 00:33:49,750
send the girl
who once walked these floors.

735
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:51,833
[window creaks]

736
00:33:52,583 --> 00:33:54,708
- [wind gusting]
- [laughter]

737
00:34:01,666 --> 00:34:02,666
[crow caws]

738
00:34:04,833 --> 00:34:05,666
[Lana yawns]

739
00:34:05,750 --> 00:34:07,500
- What time is it?
- It's late.

740
00:34:07,583 --> 00:34:09,500
I'm still parachute-lagged.

741
00:34:09,583 --> 00:34:12,041
What's this about, Luce? I need my sleep.

742
00:34:12,125 --> 00:34:16,458
My family from this world,
meet our family from another.

743
00:34:16,541 --> 00:34:18,375
Lucille Loud.

744
00:34:20,333 --> 00:34:21,708
Charmed, I'm sure.

745
00:34:21,791 --> 00:34:23,791
- [all gasp]
- G-G-Ghost!

746
00:34:23,875 --> 00:34:25,166
[grunting]

747
00:34:25,250 --> 00:34:26,750
O-M-Ghost!

748
00:34:26,833 --> 00:34:29,291
She's like a glow-in-the-dark Lucy.

749
00:34:29,375 --> 00:34:33,416
It's a pleasure to meet you,
and to be home after 400 years.

750
00:34:33,500 --> 00:34:36,083
[gasps] Dragons and ghosts?

751
00:34:36,666 --> 00:34:38,666
- This place has everything.
- Whoa.

752
00:34:38,750 --> 00:34:40,875
- She's literally floating.
- Whoa.

753
00:34:40,958 --> 00:34:43,416
- Love the see-through look.
- Wow!

754
00:34:44,125 --> 00:34:45,583
- Honey?
- What?

755
00:34:45,666 --> 00:34:48,291
We did take this trip to meet relatives.

756
00:34:48,375 --> 00:34:50,458
Yeah, but not creepy ghosty ones.

757
00:34:50,541 --> 00:34:52,250
- [gasps]
- I heard that.

758
00:34:52,333 --> 00:34:55,083
[Dad screaming]

759
00:34:56,666 --> 00:34:59,083
- [birds chirping]
- [rooster crows]

760
00:35:04,166 --> 00:35:05,166
[groans]

761
00:35:07,041 --> 00:35:11,083
- Good morning, Morag.
- Your athletic supporter, sir?

762
00:35:11,166 --> 00:35:12,791
Not mine. [laughs]

763
00:35:12,875 --> 00:35:14,000
[groans]

764
00:35:14,666 --> 00:35:16,083
Dear Old Aggie,

765
00:35:16,166 --> 00:35:19,250
